<& /page/page_title.mas, title=>"SeedQuest Help" &>

<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-body">

    <p>
      <b>SeedQuest</b> is an independent digital platform for agricultural analysis,
      field trials, and breeding support. The system is designed to help agronomists,
      breeding teams, and agricultural companies structure, analyze, and interpret
      data from real-world field experiments.
    </p>

    <p>
      This SeedQuest instance is built upon the open <b>SGN / Breedbase</b> ecosystem
      and customized for SeedQuest-specific workflows, crops, trial designs,
      and analytical approaches.
    </p>

    <p>
      SeedQuest is a <b>decision-support platform</b>. All outputs are intended to assist
      professional judgment and do not constitute guaranteed recommendations,
      regulatory guidance, or scientific publications. Users remain responsible
      for data quality, interpretation, and field-level validation.
    </p>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <b>Learning resources</b>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>
      SeedQuest intentionally preserves upstream documentation and training materials
      so users can quickly learn how to use the underlying system and its tools.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The complete Breedbase help is available in the
        <a href="https://solgenomics.github.io/sgn/" target="_new">
          Breedbase and SGN manual
        </a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Video tutorials and workshops are available on
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC3jrvvzGKKEHzOriDBgnj0A" target="_new">
          YouTube
        </a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        A technical guide for developers is available at the
        <a href="https://github.com/solgenomics/sgn/wiki/" target="_new">
          SGN developer documentation
        </a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <b>Scientific credits and citation</b>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>
      SeedQuest is built upon scientific and technical foundations developed within
      the Sol Genomics Network (SGN) and the Breedbase ecosystem, with contributions
      from multiple academic institutions, including the Boyce Thompson Institute
      and collaborating research organizations.
    </p>

    <p>
      To cite Breedbase in scientific work, please use the following publication:
    </p>

    <p>
      <b>Breedbase: a digital ecosystem for modern plant breeding</b><br/>
      Nicolas Morales, Alex C. Ogbonna, Bryan J. Ellerbrock, Guillaume J. Bauchet,
      Titima Tantikanjana, Isaak Y. Tecle, Adrian F. Powell, David Lyon, Naama Menda,
      Christiano C. Simoes, Surya Saha, Prashant Hosmani, Mirella Flores, Naftali Panitz,
      Ryan S. Preble, Afolabi Agbona, Ismail Rabbi, Peter Kulakow, Prasad Peteti,
      Robert Kawuki, Williams Esuma, Micheal Kanaabi, Doreen M. Chelangat,
      Ezenwanyi Uba, Adeyemi Olojede, Joseph Onyeka, Trushar Shah, Margaret Karanja,
      Chiedozie Egesi, Hale Tufan, Agre Paterne, Asrat Asfaw, Jean-Luc Jannink,
      Marnin Wolfe, Clay L. Birkett, David J. Waring, Jenna M. Hershberger,
      Michael A. Gore, Kelly R. Robbins, Trevor Rife, Chaney Courtney,
      Jesse Poland, Elizabeth Arnaud, Marie-Angélique Laporte, Heneriko Kulembeka,
      Kasele Salum, Emmanuel Mrema, Allan Brown, Stanley Bayo, Brigitte Uwimana,
      Violet Akech, Craig Yencho, Bert de Boeck, Hugo Campos, Rony Swennen,
      Jeremy D. Edwards, Lukas A. Mueller.<br/>
